id: pm-nnaq
title: Expose schema.unknown_field_policy via pm config set schema_unknown_field_policy
description: "schema.unknown_field_policy (allow/warn/reject) controls how item I/O handles metadata keys not in the runtime field registry. It is defined in RuntimeSchemaSettings, has defaults in constants.ts (allow), and is honored in item-format.ts, but it is not settable via pm config set. Projects that want to catch typos in field names (reject mode) or surface warnings (warn mode) must hand-edit settings.json."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[3]: "area:config","area:schema",customization
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:08:25.196Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-17T05:54:36.217Z"
author: audit-cli-schema-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- pm config set schema_unknown_field_policy allow|warn|reject updates the setting\n- pm config get schema_unknown_field_policy returns the current value\n- pm config list includes the key\n- CONFIGURATION.md documents this setting with use-case examples"
parent: pm-8jdc
risk: low
confidence: high
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-17T04:30:15.888Z",claude-code-agent,"Implemented via 1 NestedSettingDescriptor in src/core/config/nested-settings.ts: {key:schema_unknown_field_policy, path:schema.unknown_field_policy, kind:string, choices:[allow,warn,reject]}. SURPRISE: body/AC said choices were allow|warn|STRICT; the actual RUNTIME_UNKNOWN_FIELD_POLICY_VALUES (src/types.ts:47) is [allow, warn, REJECT] - used reject not strict. Path honored by validator: settings-validator.ts:312 unknown_field_policy=vOptional(vLiteral(...RUNTIME_UNKNOWN_FIELD_POLICY_VALUES)) inside schema:runtimeSchemaSettings (L428). config.ts unchanged. Tests in config-key-aliases-search.spec.ts cover set allow/warn/reject round-trip + reject of invalid 'strict'. completion.ts needs NO entry."
  "2026-06-17T05:54:36.217Z",claude-code-agent,"CodeRabbit PR#259: aligned tracker title/description/AC/body with implemented value 'reject' (spec said 'strict') + underscore key schema_unknown_field_policy so auto-changelog/docs stay consistent."
close_reason: "Added: pm config set schema_unknown_field_policy (allow|warn|reject) exposes the runtime unknown-field governance policy via NESTED_SETTING_DESCRIPTORS."
body: "## Context\n\nschema.unknown_field_policy is:\n- Defined: src/types.ts (RuntimeUnknownFieldPolicy)\n- Validated: src/core/store/settings-validator.ts\n- Honored: src/core/item/item-format.ts (unknownFieldPolicy: options.schema.unknown_field_policy)\n- Default: 'allow' (src/core/shared/constants.ts)\n- Listed in serializeSettings orderObject call (src/core/store/settings.ts)\n\nBut not in:\n- NESTED_SETTING_DESCRIPTORS (src/core/config/nested-settings.ts)\n\nAdded to NESTED_SETTING_DESCRIPTORS with kind='string' and choices=['allow','warn','reject'] following the established pattern.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- pm config set schema_unknown_field_policy allow|warn|reject updates the setting\n- pm config get schema_unknown_field_policy returns the current value\n- pm config list includes the key\n- CONFIGURATION.md documents this setting with use-case examples\n\n## Evidence\n\n- src/types.ts (RUNTIME_UNKNOWN_FIELD_POLICY_VALUES = ['allow','warn','reject'])\n- src/core/store/settings-validator.ts (vLiteral validation)\n- src/core/config/nested-settings.ts (NESTED_SETTING_DESCRIPTORS)"
